Section 6 – Data Access and Services
=====================================

We carefully considered the referee’s comments regarding scope, level of detail, and clarity of Section 6. Our revisions and decisions are as follows:

Section 6.2 (Data Access Overview):
The referee found the description of the Butler system, S3 object storage, and data dimensions difficult to follow and potentially too detailed for a data release paper. We reviewed this section extensively. While we understand the concern, we have elected to retain the material largely as written.
We have received feedback from other readers indicating that this level of detail is necessary to understand how DP1 data services operate and how to access the data effectively. Given that this is a Data Preview paper intended to introduce the community to Rubin data infrastructure, we believe this contextual information is appropriate.
We will evaluate community response and consider adjustments for future releases.

Dedicated Rubin Science Platform (RSP) Paper:
We agree that a standalone software/infrastructure paper would be valuable. A dedicated RSP paper is planned and will provide a more detailed and focused treatment of the platform and services.

Section 6.5.1 (Qserv):
Although the referee suggested moving this content to an appendix, we elected to retain it in the main text. The section is brief (~¼ page), and feedback from other readers indicates that this information is useful and interesting in the context of DP1.

Section 6.5.2 (Consolidated Database):
The Consolidated Database (ConsDB) is not currently available to the Data Rights community. As such, this section has been removed from the paper and will be reconsidered for inclusion in a future release (e.g., DP2).

Minor editorial comment:
The noted paragraph structure issue (Line 2535) has been corrected.

Overall, we have ensured that Section 6 accurately reflects the services and infrastructure that are actually available in DP1, while retaining sufficient detail to help users understand how to access and query the data.

